comment: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of MIN possession is confirmed.
Towns (MIN) sets the screen on George (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Teague (IND) makes incidental contact with Dunn (MIN) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Rubio (MIN) splits his feet on the perimeter.
Ellis (IND) sets the screen on Wiggins (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Detectable with stop watch] Dieng (MIN) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
[Incidental or immaterial] Young (IND) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Rubio (MIN) makes contact with the ball and any contact with George (IND) is considered incidental.
George (IND) sets the screen on Towns (MIN) and absorbs the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a jump ball is overturned and IND is awarded possession.
LO SLA shows George (IND) push off Dieng (MIN) to create space prior to the jump shot attempt.
LATR shows Wiggins (MIN) make contact to George's (IND) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Wiggins (MIN) moves his pivot foot heel to toe. The official is looking for any illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Dunn (MIN) sets the screen on Young (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of IND possession stands.
Dieng (MIN) makes contact with Turner (IND) that affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Turner (IND) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.

Young (IND) jumps from point A to point B into Towns (MIN) and the contact to the body affects his jump shot attempt. Young is responsible for the contact after being drawn into the air by the pump fake.
George (IND) and Wiggins (MIN) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Dunn (MIN) makes contact to Teague's (IND) arm that affects his SQBR and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Dieng (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Teague (IND) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
George (IND) makes incidental contact with Wiggins (MIN) that does not affect his FOM.
[Observable in enhanced video] Wiggins (MIN) moves his pivot foot.
Dieng (MIN) firms up his position and sets the screen on Teague (IND).
RO SLA shows that Teague (IND) makes contact to Rubio's (MIN) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Rubio (MIN) attempted a 2pt field goal when fouled is overturned to a 3pt field goal attempt.
Turner (IND) sets the screen on Wiggins (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
George (IND) sets the screen on Towns (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
